\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 03, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vei1665703135511.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vei1665703135511.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vei1665703135511.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vei1665703135511\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vei1665703135511__unifree_406377\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Free the memory that was allocated by a call to <code class=\"ph codeph\">uprmgets</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">uuf2str</code>.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"vei1665703135511__topic_d122414e1_d122415e1_d122416e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104vei1665703135511_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"vei1665703135511__codeblock_x5w_kd2_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">int unifree (UHACThAny, UVOID*pData);</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vei1665703135511__topic_d86682e1_d86683e1_d86684e1_d86685e1_d86686e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d823588e67\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"vei1665703135511__parml_bbv_ld2_bwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">hAny</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Handle of the operation or entity this data belongs to</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">pData</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">address of the allocated data</dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vei1665703135511__topic_d86687e1_d86688e1_d86689e1_d86690e1_d86691e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d823588e96\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"vei1665703135511__table_d14930e1_d14931e1_d14932e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned by unifree</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vei1665703135511__table_d14930e1_d14931e1_d14932e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vei1665703135511__table_d14930e1_d14931e1_d14932e1__entry__2\">Meaning</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vei1665703135511__table_d14930e1_d14931e1_d14932e1__entry__1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vei1665703135511__table_d14930e1_d14931e1_d14932e1__entry__2\">Success. The memory was successfully\n                        freed.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vei1665703135511__table_d14930e1_d14931e1_d14932e1__entry__1\">-165</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vei1665703135511__table_d14930e1_d14931e1_d14932e1__entry__2\">The supplied handle is not valid.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vei1665703135511__topic_d86692e1_d86693e1_d86694e1_d86695e1_d86696e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d823588e148\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vei1665703135511__d5956e20\">Library:  <span class=\"ph filepath\">ucall</span></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vei1665703135511__topic_d86697e1_d86698e1_d86699e1_d86700e1_d86701e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d823588e160\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vei1665703135511__p_d122441e1_d122442e1_d122443e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">unifree</code> should be called to\n            release memory that was allocated by a call to <code class=\"ph codeph\">uprmgets</code> or\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">uuf2str</code>. These two functions allocate memory internally and return a\n            pointer by reference. As customary with functions like this, the calling program is\n            responsible for freeing this data. Not doing so can lead to memory leaks in your\n            program.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vei1665703135511__section_o5f_rd2_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d823588e177\">Example: uuf2str, unifree, and ustr2uf</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following code calls <code class=\"ph codeph\">uuf2str</code> to retrieve string data\n            from an output parameter of one service. It then modifies the string and calls\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">ustr2uf</code> to pass it as an input parameter to another service. Note\n            that, because we want to access and modify the string, we cannot use the detach/attach\n            mechanism here. The operations OP1 and OP2 are both located in the service TESTSVC, and\n            are defined as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104vei1665703135511_html_1\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"vei1665703135511__codeblock_nhc_td2_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation op1\nparams\nstring msg : inout;\nendparams\nmsg = \"the quick brow fox jumps over the lazy dog\"\nend\n\noperation op2\nparams\nstring msg : in;\nendparams\nputmess msg\nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">And here is the 3GL routine:</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104vei1665703135511_html_2\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"vei1665703135511__codeblock_rbr_5d2_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">#include &lt;h3gl.h&gt;\n#include &lt;ctype.h&gt;\n\nvoid get_and_put ()\n{\nUHACT hEnv, hIn; /* Environment and instance handle */\nUHACT hOp1, hOp2; /* Operation handles for OP1 amd OP2 */\nlong actStatus, procErr; /* Activation status and procerr */\nUCHAR* pMsg; /* Pointer to string parameter data */\nUCHAR* p; /* Work pointer */\n\nueopen(&amp;hEnv); /* Get environment handle */\n/* Instantiate service TESTSVC */\nuinstnew (hEnv, (UCHAR *)\"TESTSVC\", 0, 0,\nUDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &amp;hIn, &amp;procErr);\nuinstopr (hIn, (UCHAR *)\"OP1\", 0, &amp;hOp1); /* Instantiate operation OP1 */\nuinstopr (hIn, (UCHAR *)\"OP2\", 0, &amp;hOp2); /* Instantiate operation OP1 */\n\nuopract (hOp1, &amp;actStatus, &amp;procErr); /* Activate operation OP1 */\nuuf2str(hOp1, 1, &amp;pMsg); /* Get a pointer to the string */\n\nfor ( p=pMsg; *p; p++ ) *p = toupper(*p);/* Convert string to uppercase*/\nustr2uf(hOp2, 1, pMsg); /* Copy string to OP2 input parameter */\nuopract (hOp2, &amp;actStatus, &amp;procErr); /* Activate operation OP2 */\n\nuinstdel (hIn, 0); /* Destroy instance */\nunifree (hOp1, pMsg); /* Free the string data */\nufreeh (&amp;hOp1); /* Free OP1 operation handle */\nufreeh (&amp;hOp2); /* Free OP2 operation handle */\nufreeh (&amp;hIn); /* Free instance handle */\nufreeh (&amp;hEnv); /* Free environment handle */\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/khn1665702693426.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uprmgets</a><p>Return Uniface-formatted data from a basic parameter or entity field.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mmr1665702693499.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uuf2str</a><p>Get a pointer to the string data in a basic parameter or entity field.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532980\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532980\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "unifree Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 03, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Free the memory that was allocated by a call to uprmgets or uuf2str . Explain this code int unifree (UHACThAny, UVOID*pData); Copy Parameters hAny Handle of the operation or entity this data belongs to pData address of the allocated data Return Values Table 1. Values returned by unifree Value Meaning 0 Success. The memory was successfully freed. -165 The supplied handle is not valid. Use Library: ucall Description unifree should be called to release memory that was allocated by a call to uprmgets or uuf2str . These two functions allocate memory internally and return a pointer by reference. As customary with functions like this, the calling program is responsible for freeing this data. Not doing so can lead to memory leaks in your program. Example: uuf2str, unifree, and ustr2uf The following code calls uuf2str to retrieve string data from an output parameter of one service. It then modifies the string and calls ustr2uf to pass it as an input parameter to another service. Note that, because we want to access and modify the string, we cannot use the detach/attach mechanism here. The operations OP1 and OP2 are both located in the service TESTSVC, and are defined as follows: Explain this code operation op1 params string msg : inout; endparams msg = \"the quick brow fox jumps over the lazy dog\" end operation op2 params string msg : in; endparams putmess msg end Copy And here is the 3GL routine: Explain this code #include <h3gl.h> #include <ctype.h> void get_and_put () { UHACT hEnv, hIn; /* Environment and instance handle */ UHACT hOp1, hOp2; /* Operation handles for OP1 amd OP2 */ long actStatus, procErr; /* Activation status and procerr */ UCHAR* pMsg; /* Pointer to string parameter data */ UCHAR* p; /* Work pointer */ ueopen(&hEnv); /* Get environment handle */ /* Instantiate service TESTSVC */ uinstnew (hEnv, (UCHAR *)\"TESTSVC\", 0, 0, UDEFAULT_COMM_MODE, 0, &hIn, &procErr); uinstopr (hIn, (UCHAR *)\"OP1\", 0, &hOp1); /* Instantiate operation OP1 */ uinstopr (hIn, (UCHAR *)\"OP2\", 0, &hOp2); /* Instantiate operation OP1 */ uopract (hOp1, &actStatus, &procErr); /* Activate operation OP1 */ uuf2str(hOp1, 1, &pMsg); /* Get a pointer to the string */ for ( p=pMsg; *p; p++ ) *p = toupper(*p);/* Convert string to uppercase*/ ustr2uf(hOp2, 1, pMsg); /* Copy string to OP2 input parameter */ uopract (hOp2, &actStatus, &procErr); /* Activate operation OP2 */ uinstdel (hIn, 0); /* Destroy instance */ unifree (hOp1, pMsg); /* Free the string data */ ufreeh (&hOp1); /* Free OP1 operation handle */ ufreeh (&hOp2); /* Free OP2 operation handle */ ufreeh (&hIn); /* Free instance handle */ ufreeh (&hEnv); /* Free environment handle */ } Copy Related Links uprmgets Return Uniface-formatted data from a basic parameter or entity field. uuf2str Get a pointer to the string data in a basic parameter or entity field. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}